<div id="p530" class="blockpost roweven">
<h2><span><span class="conr">#8</span> <a href="viewtopic.php?pid=530#p530">2017-03-10 22:06:24</a></span></h2>
<div class="box">
<div class="inbox">
<div class="postbody">
<div class="postleft">
<dl>
<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=7068">nanok0de</a></strong></dt>
<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Unconfirmed Member</strong></dd>
<dd><span>Registered: 2017-03-10</span></dd>
<dd><span>Posts: 2</span></dd>
</dl>
</div>
<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: [SOLVED] Annoying Random Logout</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>Guys I think we found the solution thanks to @gnugr @netpanda and @Alexandrosmouhtsis on the Telegram Parrot Group, I&#039;ve tried many solutions such as reinstalling the system, installing drivers and stuff... anyway none of them worked for me. But I noticed something in my &#039;dmesg&#039; output:</p><p>[12.628205] [dmr:intel_enable_lvds [i915]] *ERROR* timed out waiting for panel to power on.</p><p>Well... I just added this line to the &#039;/etc/default/grub&#039; file:</p><p>GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT=&quot;quiet i915.modeset=0&quot;</p><p>then run &#039;update-grub&#039;, then rebooted, and voila, the issue was gone.</p><p>Hope this works on your system too.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="inbox">
